<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FD3FE5D48A7566AFE2BFD09" pageId="413" pageNumber="414" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FD3FE5D48A7566AFCB6FD24" blockId="413.[151,1436,326,911]" pageId="413" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FD3FE5D48A7566AFE08FEAF" bold="true" box="[151,429,326,351]" pageId="413" pageNumber="414">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FD3FE5D4AB6566AFCB6FEAE" box="[646,787,326,350]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="413" pageNumber="414" unit="mm" value="2.85" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.5">2.5–3.2 mm</quantity>
. Testaceous-reddish, except petiole and metasoma black and antennal segments 3–10 brown. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 8:5:12:7:6:6:5:5:5:7. Head excavated, dull, granulated; frontal line complete; occipital carina absent; POL = 1.5; OL = 2.5; OOL = 7.5. Palpal formula 5/2. Pronotum shiny, weakly granulated, crossed by strong transverse impression. Scutum shiny, sculptured by some longitudinal keels. Metanotum short, about as long as scutellum, not hollow behind scutellum. Metathorax + propodeum dull, with anterior surface granulated and posterior surface transversely striate; anterior surface with track of median longitudinal furrow. Mesopleura and metapleura transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture obsolete. Protarsal segments in following proportions: 13:2.5:3.5:13:21. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FD3FE5D4A19555DFD0BFD79" box="[553,686,625,649]" captionStart="PLATE 129" captionStartId="412.[151,233,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[251,1360,292,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-100@412.[151,1436,267,1919]" captionTargetPageId="412" captionText="PLATE 129. A–C, E. Chelae. D. Vertex of head. A. Gonatopus medius, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B. G.mysorensis, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C. G. nivosus (=G. delhiensis Olmi) from India (from Olmi 1987c). D, E. G. perpolitus, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.35 mm for A, 0.25 mm for B, 0.22 mm for C, 0.61 mm for D and 0.17 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278828/files/figure.png" pageId="413" pageNumber="414">Plate 129B</figureCitation>
) with one small subapical tooth and six–eight peg-like hairs. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FD3FE5D498A55BAFD9EFD5E" box="[442,571,662,686]" captionStart="PLATE 129" captionStartId="412.[151,233,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[251,1360,292,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-100@412.[151,1436,267,1919]" captionTargetPageId="412" captionText="PLATE 129. A–C, E. Chelae. D. Vertex of head. A. Gonatopus medius, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B. G.mysorensis, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C. G. nivosus (=G. delhiensis Olmi) from India (from Olmi 1987c). D, E. G. perpolitus, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.35 mm for A, 0.25 mm for B, 0.22 mm for C, 0.61 mm for D and 0.17 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278828/files/figure.png" pageId="413" pageNumber="414">Plate 129B</figureCitation>
) with inner margin proximally serrated, with one row of 16–21 lamellae; distal apex with about nine lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FD3FE5D48F755CDFE2BFD09" blockId="413.[151,1436,326,911]" box="[199,398,737,761]" pageId="413" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FD3FE5D48F755CDFEAEFD09" bold="true" box="[199,267,737,761]" pageId="413" pageNumber="414">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
